    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Accounts detailing the process of probate including inventories, final expenses, and the dispensation of property. Historical probate accounts were mostly filed by women and therefore these accounts provide unique information on women's experience in handling property and the history of property relations between men and women.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046996/Oxford Dictionary of Local and Family History [online] (2003)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Documenten met bijzonderheden over de testamentaire procedure, met inbegrip van inventarislijsten, definitieve kosten en de verdeling van de eigendommen. In vroeger tijden werden boedelbeschrijvingen meestal ingediend door vrouwen, en ze geven dan ook unieke informatie over de ervaringen van vrouwen met het beheer van bezittingen, alsmede de geschiedenis van de relaties tussen mannen en vrouwen betreffende hun bezittingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099090/Van Dale Online Woordenboek (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>詳細說明遺囑認證過程的帳目，包括財產目錄、最終開支，和資產的分配。過去多由女性提出遺囑帳目，因此這些帳目可提供女性進行資產處置的獨特資料，以及與男女間資產關係有關的歷史訊息。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bericht über die Einzelheiten einer Erbschaftsangelegenheit, einschließlich Verzeichnissen, den Aufwendungen und der Verteilung des Besitzes. Historische Nachlassaufstellungen wurden meist von Frauen besorgt und dienen deshalb als einzigartige Informationsquelle über die Erfahrungen von Frauen bei der Eigentumsverwaltung und die Geschichte der Eigentumsverhältnisse zwischen Männern und Frauen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
